Campy. Over the top. Fun. Not at all scary. More comedic.
For a dark comedy/cheesy horror movie, this one does the trick! It's a little off-the-wall, but funny and twisted...which is just my style!

This ditty was extremely enjoyable.  The plot was well played out and the acting was great.  However, why the creators of this film added this zany, drunken singer as the Ferguson's next-door-neighbor I'll never know.  He was disgusting and added nothing to the thread of this film.  He must have been a friend or financier to someone on this project.  I took away three points for this fatal mistake.

Wholesome suburban family has unusual zest for life.  What's their secret?  They're cannibals! They eat neighbors who push them too far. This family doesn't get mad, they get full!  (brief gore, brief nudity, violence, language, drugs)
